           SPELL=xfig
         VERSION=3.2.4
          SOURCE=${SPELL}.${VERSION}.full.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}.${VERSION}
   SOURCE_URL[0]=ftp://www-epb.lbl.gov/xfig/${SOURCE}
          MD5[0]=e1fff790c242856d64fadc99c205db52
        WEB_SITE=http://www.xfig.org
         ENTERED=20020210
         UPDATED=20050420
      LICENSE[0]=PD
       BUILD_API=2
           SHORT="An X Window System tool for drawing basic vector graphics."
cat << EOF
Xfig is an X Window System tool for creating basic vector graphics,
including bezier curves, lines, rulers and more.  The resulting
graphics can be saved, printed on PostScript printers or converted to
a variety of other formats (e.g., X11 bitmaps, Encapsulated
PostScript, LaTeX).
EOF
